  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "RESIDENT TECHICAL OFFICER (M&E)",
  "description": "<p>1. To supervise M&amp;E installation works and sign off form of supervision/testing ensuring contractor’s work are executed according to contract specifications, drawings, MOS, etc</p>\n<p>2. To check and ensure accuracy of electrical works, including necessary testing of installation and instrument before building LEW sign off</p>\n<p>3. To check and verify materials used by contractor are only of approved type materials</p>\n<p>4. To check and verify as-built drawings submitted by contractor accurately reflects the site work</p>\n<p>5. To attend the weekly meeting with consultant and Client</p>\n<p>6. To work with contractor to identify the existing service and new works and ensure contractor carry out works as according to code of practice and consultant design intent</p>\n<p>7. To attend to urgent matter on site, and highlight/report any discrepancies or work not properly done by contractor</p>\n<p>8. To ensure the contractor safety officer is performing the safety check</p>\n<p>9. To assist and report to M&amp;E Engineer the daily works on site, including maintaining daily site work records/reports, based on working days, and highlight/report any discrepancies or work not properly done by contractor</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
